ce:section.ce:para:
The bacterial detection efficiency of prepared CQDs was studied against gram negative (E. coli) bacteria. For the analysis, bacteria culture of E. coli was kept in nutrient broth and concentration was estimated by colony formation method (Fig. 5
                        ). Around 100 μL of each type of CQDs solution was poured to the centrifuge tube containing 1000 μL of different concentrations of E. coli suspension. The formed solutions were set for incubation at 37 °C for 1 h. Afterwards, each suspension was centrifuged at 8000 rpm for 7 min to isolate the conjugate of E. coli with CQDs. Subsequently, the supernatants of the each of the mixture were estimated for fluorescence bacterial detection. The fluorescence intensities were recorded at 310 nm for the purpose of quantification (Fig. 6
                        ). Under the optimized experimental conditions, fluorescence signals of different concentrations of CQDs labelled E. coli bacteria (0–40 × 108 cfu mL−1) were analyzed by using the fluorescence spectroscopy.
